text:
Ordered in from Corleone's tonight. I've never eaten there before, so I didn't know what to expect. Here is what was good:  
1- ordering through the Yelp app was very easy and my order arrived earlier than scheduled and was delivered by a very nice person;
2- our onion rings were super crispy and wonderful and they accommodated our request for lots of extra ketchup;
3- our antipasto salad was simple and fresh and came with chips and a drink.

Not so good:
We were going to share the buffalo chicken sandwich... but ended up not being what either one of us expected or enjoyed. It was finally minced chicken, smothered in buffalo sauce, and stuffed into soft hero bread doused in blue cheese dressing. The way they did the meat was just odd. Granted, the Yelp app did not provide any description of the sandwich beyond the name, and I chose to order it anyway, so it was my own fault for assuming that it was going to be different from what I received. Nonetheless it grossed us both out and left me feeling like despite the positives, I probably would not order from this restaurant again.
